Title: Counting Coprime Pairs
Description: Given a list of n positive integers, your task is to count the number of pairs of integers that are coprime (i.e., their greatest common divisor is one).
Input Specification:
The first input line has an integer n: the number of elements. 
 The next line has n integers x_1,x_2,\dots,x_n: the contents of the list.
Output Specification: Print one integer: the answer for the task.
